🧠 Models

This directory contains the artificial intelligence frameworks developed for the diagnosis and prognostic stratification of head and neck small round blue cell neoplasms (SRBCNs).

The repository includes:
* XGBoost multiclass classification and SHAP explainability analysis
* CellViT++ nuclear segmentation and cellular representation
* Multimodal deep learning architectures
* Foundation model pipelines (UNI and Virchow)
* Survival analysis
* XGBoost survival prediction

The framework integrates clinicopathological variables, nuclear morphometric features, histopathological image representations, and foundation model embeddings within a unified computational pathology pipeline.

📊 XGBoost Multiclass Classification and SHAP
Classification of tumour groups using clinicopathological and nuclear morphometric variables.

Input features
* Age
* Sex
* Anatomical location
* Nuclear area
* Nuclear perimeter
* Nuclear circularity
* Nuclear eccentricity

Output
* Multiclass classification
* SHAP feature importance
* ROC curves
* Confusion matrices

🔬 CellViT++ Nuclear Segmentation and Cellular Representation
Transformer-based nuclear segmentation and cellular feature extraction.

Outputs
* Nuclear masks
* Cell embeddings
* Morphometric descriptors

Extracted features
* Nuclear area
* Nuclear perimeter
* Nuclear circularity
* Nuclear eccentricity

🧬 Multimodal Deep Learning Architectures

Integration of image features, morphometric descriptors, and clinicopathological variables.

CNN backbones
* AlexNet
* MobileNet
* InceptionV3
* DenseNet121
* Xception
* ResNet50

🚀 Foundation Models (UNI and Virchow)

Vision transformer-based pathology foundation models used for histopathological representation learning.

Outputs
* Feature embeddings
* Classification probabilities
* Patient-level predictions

Best-performing model
* Virchow
  * Internal AUROC: 0.981
  * External AUROC: 0.972

⏳ Survival Analysis

Conventional survival analysis using:
* Kaplan–Meier curves
* Log-rank tests
* Cox proportional hazards models

🤖 XGBoost Survival Prediction

Machine learning-based survival modelling using the Cox objective function.

Outputs
* Risk scores
* Survival predictions
* SHAP survival interpretation

Performance
* Training C-index: 0.976
* Validation C-index: 0.788
* Test C-index: 0.768
